meta {
  name: Create Page/Form Org Mapping
  type: http
  seq: 9
}

post {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/meta/page-org-map
  body: json
  auth: none
}

headers {
  Cookie: auth_token={{authToken}}
}

body:json {
  {
    "org_id": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000",
    "page_id": "123456789",
    "form_id": "2217695302333588",
    "platform": "fb"
  }
}

docs {
  Registers which org a Meta Page+Form combination belongs to — requires
  tenant_admin rank or higher. Required before any lead from that form can
  be synced: the webhook resolves org_id by looking up (tenant_id, form_id)
  here, falling back to (tenant_id, page_id) for brand-new forms on an
  already-mapped Page.

  A form belongs to exactly one Page in Meta's data model, but a Page can
  run many forms across different orgs/campaigns — so form_id is unique
  per mapping (uq_meta_page_form_org_map on (page_id, form_id)), while an
  org can own many rows here (multiple pages and/or multiple forms).
}
